00:18:07,800 --> 00:18:12,840
 made Jing Xi Chi painfully aware of reality. 

260
00:18:13,620 --> 00:18:18,900
 He didn't want us to go because he was worried about affecting our studies; 

261
00:18:18,900 --> 00:18:24,350
 he didn't want us to see him like this. Afraid and uncertain. 

262
00:18:55,520 --> 00:18:57,580
Oh my God.

263
00:18:57,580 --> 00:19:00,140
This is a huge challenge.

264
00:19:08,540 --> 00:19:12,390
 Honestly, I can't even tell who's right and who's wrong anymore. 

265
00:19:12,390 --> 00:19:14,480
 Absolutely no clue. 

266
00:19:14,480 --> 00:19:18,329
 But I will definitely find enough evidence to prove to him 

267
00:19:18,329 --> 00:19:22,020
 that the road ahead is still long and that everything can start over. 

268
00:19:22,020 --> 00:19:25,010
 There's still time for everything. 

269
00:19:43,870 --> 00:19:46,520
- Let me help you. 
 - No, it's fine. No need.

270
00:19:46,520 --> 00:19:48,020
I can do it myself.

271
00:19:48,020 --> 00:19:51,540
- Where's Cong? 
 - The teacher called him away.

272
00:19:51,540 --> 00:19:53,670
What, you want Cong to help you?

273
00:19:53,670 --> 00:19:56,640
No, I was just thinking...

274
00:19:56,640 --> 00:19:58,590
His big brother is back in school now.

275
00:19:58,590 --> 00:20:00,200
Shouldn't he personally come to greet me?

276
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:03,060
   

277
00:20:03,060 --> 00:20:04,580
I'm fine. I can do it.

278
00:20:04,580 --> 00:20:07,120
- It's okay. Let me help. 
 - No need, really.

279
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:29,230
If you don't want to go back to class, I can stay here with you for a bit.

280
00:20:29,780 --> 00:20:35,870
I used to do pull-ups on the goalpost, and the coach would tell me off.

281
00:20:36,580 --> 00:20:38,430
He said it wasn't solid.

282
00:20:46,340 --> 00:20:48,160
Jing Xi Chi...

283
00:20:48,870 --> 00:20:51,050
how old are you this year?

284
00:20:55,540 --> 00:20:57,180
Did you fry your brain?

285
00:20:57,180 --> 00:20:59,680
I'm only a few months older than you.

286
00:20:59,680 --> 00:21:01,390
You're 17 years old, right?

287
00:21:01,390 --> 00:21:03,130
Obviously.

288
00:21:03,740 --> 00:21:05,890
Do you know Baggio?

289
00:21:05,890 --> 00:21:09,800
When he was 17, Baggio suffered a ligament tear on his right knee.

290
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:11,310
He had 220 stitches.

291
00:21:11,310 --> 00:21:13,460
In total, he underwent six surgeries.

292
00:21:13,460 --> 00:21:18,150
Finally, at the age of 28, he made his Champions League debut.

293
00:21:18,150 --> 00:21:21,870
In 1998, Piero also suffered a ligament tear.

294
00:21:21,870 --> 00:21:27,460
In 2006, he scored a hat-trick during the second half of Italy's quarterfinals.

295
00:21:27,460 --> 00:21:32,110
In 1999, Ronaldo suffered a complete rupture of his cruciate ligament.

296
00:21:32,110 --> 00:21:34,310
When everyone thought he would retire,

297
00:21:34,310 --> 00:21:39,320
he returned in the 2001-2002 season with an improved form.

298
00:21:39,320 --> 00:21:43,890
In 2006, Owen tore his ligament.

299
00:21:43,890 --> 00:21:47,520
In 2008, he became the captain of Newscal.

300
00:21:47,520 --> 00:21:49,290
Newcastle.

301
00:21:57,890 --> 00:21:59,550
Captain of Newcastle, yes.

302
00:21:59,550 --> 00:22:01,550
He scored 11 goals that season.

303
00:22:01,550 --> 00:22:04,070
- Chen Huan Er. 
 - In 1999, the UEFA Cup.

304
00:22:04,070 --> 00:22:05,320
- At Celtic Park... 
 - Chen Huan Er.

305
00:22:05,320 --> 00:22:07,546
Larsson suffered a double leg fracture.

306
00:22:07,546 --> 00:22:10,240
- In the following season, he made it— 
 - Huan Er.

307
00:22:14,740 --> 00:22:16,460
Thank you.

308
00:22:26,350 --> 00:22:29,220
 Actually, I'm a very forgetful person. 

309
00:22:29,220 --> 00:22:32,920
 I stay optimistic by leaving the past behind, 

310
00:22:32,920 --> 00:22:37,700
 but no matter how much time has passed, I will always remember this morning. 

311
00:22:38,420 --> 00:22:42,310
 This ever-refreshing morning made me believe 

312
00:22:42,310 --> 00:22:49,590
 that only when we lose the courage to start over does youth truly come to an end. 

313
00:22:57,520 --> 00:22:58,620
Are you going back?

314
00:22:58,620 --> 00:23:00,110
Let me see that cheat sheet you wrote.

315
00:23:00,110 --> 00:23:02,550
Jing Xi Chi! Give it back!

316
00:23:02,550 --> 00:23:04,590
Why did you write so much?

317
00:23:23,070 --> 00:23:27,550
Xi Chi, when your leg heals,

318
00:23:29,840 --> 00:23:31,900
do you still want to play soccer?

319
00:23:41,110 --> 00:23:44,360
Dad, you know what?

320
00:23:46,120 --> 00:23:52,190
I don't really remember clearly how I started playing soccer in the first place.

321
00:23:53,700 --> 00:23:58,260
It feels like ever since I could remember,

322
00:24:00,180 --> 00:24:02,660
 I've loved playing. 

323
00:24:03,980 --> 00:24:10,560
 Mom always told me that it was also the dream you never got to fulfill when you were young. 

324
00:24:10,560 --> 00:24:12,870
 As a kid, I didn't really understand. 

325
00:24:12,870 --> 00:24:17,560
 You told me to train, so I just followed along. 

326
00:24:21,550 --> 00:24:24,860
Your mom cares too much about you.

327
00:24:24,860 --> 00:24:27,110
She's afraid you'll get hurt.

328
00:24:28,280 --> 00:24:34,930
She said every time she watched you play, her heart was in her throat.

329
00:24:37,630 --> 00:24:39,830
Mom has watched me play?

330
00:24:40,620 --> 00:24:42,300
All right.

331
00:24:43,520 --> 00:24:46,630
No matter what, remember our promise.

332
00:24:46,630 --> 00:24:51,560
No matter what happens, stick it out until the end.

333
00:24:57,260 --> 00:25:00,630
Let's go home, okay?

334
00:25:00,630 --> 00:25:02,180
Come on.

335
00:25:02,740 --> 00:25:04,560
Take it slow.

336
00:25:05,427 --> 00:25:08,080
- Don't put too much pressure on that foot. 
 - I'm fine, Dad.

337
00:25:10,180 --> 00:25:12,420
- You okay? 
 - Yeah.

338
00:25:28,150 --> 00:25:29,960
Mom...

339
00:25:33,480 --> 00:25:38,679
I just got off work and happened to pass by, so I'll go home with you.

340
00:25:38,679 --> 00:25:40,940
Didn't you say you wouldn't come?

341
00:25:42,250 --> 00:25:44,070
Listen to yourself.

342
00:25:44,070 --> 00:25:45,730
It's not like Xi Chi is playing.

343
00:25:45,730 --> 00:25:48,010
What's there to watch?

344
00:26:00,840 --> 00:26:04,440
Yesterday, your school coach called.

345
00:26:04,440 --> 00:26:09,771
He said the youth team coach asked about you and wanted to visit.

346
00:26:09,771 --> 00:26:11,500
They think you have a lot of potential.

347
00:26:11,500 --> 00:26:15,560
I thanked them and told them not to come

348
00:26:21,830 --> 00:26:23,870
until you've fully recovered.

349
00:26:23,870 --> 00:26:25,740
Once you're better,

350
00:26:26,980 --> 00:26:31,080
I'll personally take you to visit them.

351
00:26:35,160 --> 00:26:36,750
Mom.

352
00:26:39,630 --> 00:26:41,260
Thank you.

353
00:26:44,980 --> 00:26:46,660
I've thought it through, too.

354
00:26:46,660 --> 00:26:51,240
I'm letting go. From now on, you'll make your own decisions.

355
00:26:51,240 --> 00:26:54,709
I used to meddle too much, worrying and running around for nothing,

356
00:26:54,709 --> 00:26:56,740
and it didn't help.

357
00:26:59,870 --> 00:27:01,360
Mom.

358
00:27:03,110 --> 00:27:06,070
I was never mad at you.

359
00:27:07,500 --> 00:27:09,940
I knew in my heart.

360
00:27:09,940 --> 00:27:14,590
If you weren't the one playing the serious role in this family,

361
00:27:14,590 --> 00:27:19,860
with Dad and me being so overly dramatic, we'd have turned the house upside down sooner or later.

362
00:27:27,500 --> 00:27:29,150
All right, now.

363
00:27:29,150 --> 00:27:31,260
Let's go home.

364
00:27:31,260 --> 00:27:33,700
We don't want to make your mom cry.

365
00:27:39,310 --> 00:27:40,600
- Slowly. 
 - Be careful.

366
00:27:40,600 --> 00:27:42,120
Okay.

367
00:27:58,500 --> 00:28:00,840
Did you hear what I said?

368
00:28:00,840 --> 00:28:04,630
Your dad is away on a business trip, so I'll take you to school for these few days.

369
00:28:04,630 --> 00:28:05,910
You don't have to.

370
00:28:05,910 --> 00:28:07,540
Why? How will you get there then?

371
00:28:07,540 --> 00:28:09,940
It's fine. Don't worry about it.

372
00:28:13,760 --> 00:28:14,920
   

373
00:28:23,300 --> 00:28:25,640
   

374
00:28:27,800 --> 00:28:29,350
Mom.

375
00:28:30,127 --> 00:28:31,832
Mom.

376
00:28:31,832 --> 00:28:34,002
Explain this to me?

377
00:28:36,020 --> 00:28:39,120
Actually, I did have a meeting that day.

378
00:28:39,120 --> 00:28:41,133
I planned to tell you guys and go together,

379
00:28:41,133 --> 00:28:43,840
but I was afraid I wouldn't make it and didn't want to disappoint you.

380
00:28:43,840 --> 00:28:45,980
So, as soon as the meeting ended, I rushed over,

381
00:28:45,980 --> 00:28:47,910
but it was already over.

382
00:28:49,280 --> 00:28:51,420
Then where did you get this ticket?

383
00:28:51,420 --> 00:28:53,830
Huan Er gave it to me.

384
00:28:53,830 --> 00:28:55,400
Thanks, Mom.

385
00:28:59,480 --> 00:29:00,914
Wait!

386
00:29:00,914 --> 00:29:02,870
Let me keep it as a souvenir.

387
00:29:02,870 --> 00:29:04,790
Give it to me.

388
00:29:09,100 --> 00:29:10,790
I should have invited her to come with us.

389
00:29:10,790 --> 00:29:12,700
What did you say?

390
00:29:14,020 --> 00:29:15,070
Nothing.

391
00:29:15,070 --> 00:29:19,550
From now on, after school, I'll be walking home with Huan Er and Cong. Rest assured.

392
00:29:19,550 --> 00:29:22,920
- Slowly. 
 - I'm okay. My leg is fine.

393
00:29:22,920 --> 00:29:25,470
Gosh, this kid...

394
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:46,360
   

395
00:29:55,940 --> 00:30:00,240
   

396
00:30:21,400 --> 00:30:22,500
   

397
00:30:22,500 --> 00:30:23,880
   

398
00:30:32,110 --> 00:30:33,590
Hello, what's up?

399
00:30:33,590 --> 00:30:36,760
 Chen Huan Er, some tricks you've got there. 

400
00:30:36,760 --> 00:30:39,070
Come clean now!

401
00:30:39,070 --> 00:30:42,740
Tell me. Where did you get so many tickets from?

402
00:30:42,740 --> 00:30:45,020
I got them from Coach Li.

403
00:30:45,910 --> 00:30:49,560
 Pay attention to your steps! Faster, faster! 

404
00:30:50,350 --> 00:30:51,700
 What are you doing? 

405
00:30:51,700 --> 00:30:53,630
 Watch your step! 

406
00:30:53,630 --> 00:30:54,870
 Hello, sir. 

407
00:30:54,870 --> 00:30:58,110
 The tickets for Sunday's finals. Can I have one? 

408
00:30:58,110 --> 00:31:00,010
 Sure. Help yourself. 

409
00:31:01,220 --> 00:31:03,870
 - Next. Hurry up! 
 - Thanks. 

410
00:31:05,320 --> 00:31:07,560
 I'm taking three. 

411
00:31:09,020 --> 00:31:11,160
 Hey, are you listening? Did you not eat breakfast this morning? 

412
00:31:11,160 --> 00:31:12,380
It was that easy?

413
00:31:12,380 --> 00:31:13,434
 What did you think? 

414
00:31:13,434 --> 00:31:17,010
Did you think I had to beg on my knees just to get the tickets?

415
00:31:20,150 --> 00:31:22,390
Okay. Never mind, just asking.

416
00:31:22,390 --> 00:31:24,700
That's all. Bye.

417
00:31:36,110 --> 00:31:37,210
Take it slow. Be careful.

418
00:31:37,210 --> 00:31:40,020
I'm fine, Mom. I'm almost fully recovered.

419
00:31:40,020 --> 00:31:43,260
- Good morning, Aunt Lin. 
 - Morning, Huan Er.

420
00:31:43,260 --> 00:31:46,520
Jing Xi Chi, I'll take you today.

421
00:31:46,520 --> 00:31:47,840
Didn't Cong say he'd take me?

422
00:31:47,840 --> 00:31:50,840
The teacher asked him to go for a competition.

423
00:31:50,840 --> 00:31:54,940
Why don't I call a cab for you guys?

424
00:31:54,940 --> 00:31:56,959
It's okay. We can get there on the bike.

425
00:31:56,959 --> 00:31:59,150
You're going to be late for work. Don't worry about us.

426
00:31:59,150 --> 00:32:00,260
Okay, I'm going to be late.

427
00:32:00,260 --> 00:32:02,160
I'll leave him to you. You guys figure it out.

428
00:32:02,160 --> 00:32:03,960
- I'll handle it. 
 - Thank you.

429
00:32:03,960 --> 00:32:06,720
- Call a cab if you need to. 
 - Don't worry.

430
00:32:07,970 --> 00:32:10,690
Come on, get on.

431
00:32:11,310 --> 00:32:12,790
You even added a back seat for me?

432
00:32:12,790 --> 00:32:14,350
That's right.

433
00:32:14,350 --> 00:32:17,080
Aren't I considerate? Don't want your butt to bruise.

434
00:32:17,080 --> 00:32:18,800
Come on then.

435
00:32:19,920 --> 00:32:21,816
Are you sure you can do it?

436
00:32:21,816 --> 00:32:24,310
Why not? Just get on and see.

437
00:32:24,310 --> 00:32:26,560
Give me your bag then.

438
00:32:26,560 --> 00:32:28,310
No biggie. I can still ride with the bag.

439
00:32:28,310 --> 00:32:31,140
- I'm going to get on. 
 - Go on.

440
00:32:31,140 --> 00:32:32,550
Here, take a seat.

441
00:32:32,550 --> 00:32:34,020
- Sit tight. 
 - Here I go.

442
00:32:34,020 --> 00:32:35,590
- Hang on. 
 - Okay, go ahead.

443
00:32:35,590 --> 00:32:38,560
- I'm going to go fast. 
 - Not too fast, please.

444
00:32:38,560 --> 00:32:41,280
- My leg just healed. 
 - I'll be lightning fast.

445
00:32:47,910 --> 00:32:49,500
Are you tired?

446
00:32:50,220 --> 00:32:51,350
No.

447
00:32:51,350 --> 00:32:53,660
This is nothing.

448
00:32:53,660 --> 00:32:55,150
Chen Huan Er...

449
00:32:55,150 --> 00:33:01,690
even though you added such an ugly back seat to my beloved bike, I'm actually pretty touched.

450
00:33:02,580 --> 00:33:06,765
But at this speed, when are we ever going to get to school?

451
00:33:06,765 --> 00:33:09,150
- Well, you could take a taxi. 
 - No, no, no.

452
00:33:09,150 --> 00:33:10,700
I'm a disabled man.

453
00:33:10,700 --> 00:33:13,110
Even if I'm late, I have a legitimate excuse.

454
00:33:13,110 --> 00:33:15,940
But I don't, bro.

455
00:33:15,940 --> 00:33:20,440
Exactly. So you better hurry up and push, or you're going to get punished.

456
00:33:20,440 --> 00:33:22,420
- Don't just stand there. Push! 
 - I...

457
00:33:22,420 --> 00:33:24,200
Let's go! Hurry up!

458
00:33:24,200 --> 00:33:26,390
- Ugh, you're so annoying. 
 - Careful! Don't make me fall.

459
00:33:26,390 --> 00:33:27,800
Faster.

460
00:33:45,310 --> 00:33:48,660
 That morning on the way to school, I don't even know how long it took. 

461
00:33:48,660 --> 00:33:53,800
 And even though he says everything's back to normal, I could tell 

462
00:33:53,800 --> 00:33:59,420
 his recovery is dragging out much longer than before. 

463
00:34:28,200 --> 00:34:30,870
 But Jing Xi Chi would never say something cheesy like, 

464
00:34:30,870 --> 00:34:33,830
 "Pain is what makes youth real." 

465
00:34:33,830 --> 00:34:38,710
 He'd just scoff, call it dramatic, and get right back to it. 

466
00:34:53,310 --> 00:34:55,350
Look here, Jing Xi Chi.

467
00:34:55,350 --> 00:34:57,600
Look here.

468
00:34:57,600 --> 00:35:02,240
- What? 
 - Mountain pose. My dad taught me.

469
00:35:03,420 --> 00:35:07,310
Stop kicking. Your leg has only just healed.

470
00:35:07,310 --> 00:35:12,000
You have no idea how many rounds my heart's been flying on the field.

471
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:15,370
Anyway, the physical therapist said that I'm recovering well.

472
00:35:15,370 --> 00:35:18,640
He said I could try out for the upcoming special training recruitment.

473
00:35:18,640 --> 00:35:22,640
You have no clue how much I miss the smell of the lawn.

474
00:35:23,940 --> 00:35:25,790
Lawn?

475
00:35:25,790 --> 00:35:28,200
You miss the smell of grass?

476
00:35:28,200 --> 00:35:30,500
Okay. I'll satisfy your wish.

477
00:35:30,500 --> 00:35:32,830
You miss grass, right? Here, have a whiff.

478
00:35:32,830 --> 00:35:35,390
- I know you know the smell of grass. 
 - It's prickling my face!

479
00:35:35,390 --> 00:35:37,110
- Doesn't it smell good? 
 - Chen Huan Er!

480
00:35:37,110 --> 00:35:38,640
- Don't you like it? 
 - I don't like this.

481
00:35:38,640 --> 00:35:40,320
I want a lawn, not just grass! Why get me this?

482
00:35:40,320 --> 00:35:43,340
- It's nice! You like it, huh? 
 - I'll end up with allergies.

483
00:35:43,340 --> 00:35:46,020
- I don't want this. 
 - I know you like it.

484
00:35:46,020 --> 00:35:49,690
- You like it so much! 
 - No, I don't.

485
00:36:09,100 --> 00:36:10,350
Hello?

486
00:36:10,350 --> 00:36:13,420
 Hi. The orthopedic book you asked for last time has arrived. 

487
00:36:13,420 --> 00:36:15,870
 You can pick it up when you're free. 

488
00:36:16,450 --> 00:36:19,350
Thanks. I'll come get it tomorrow.

489
00:36:53,310 --> 00:36:57,240
- You're here. 
 - Hey, the book I ordered...

490
00:37:01,830 --> 00:37:02,830
Here.

491
00:37:02,830 --> 00:37:05,670
Thanks. It's 150, right?

492
00:37:05,670 --> 00:37:07,350
180.

493
00:37:08,060 --> 00:37:10,520
Wasn't it 150?

494
00:37:10,520 --> 00:37:12,054
This book is out of print.

495
00:37:12,054 --> 00:37:16,780
I had to check with multiple publishers to find it, so there's a markup.

496
00:37:16,780 --> 00:37:18,640
Then why didn't you mention that over the phone?

497
00:37:18,640 --> 00:37:20,380
Do you want it or not?

498
00:37:27,750 --> 00:37:32,160
I didn't bring enough money. Can I pay you the rest next time?

499
00:37:34,980 --> 00:37:36,850
I'll cover it.

500
00:37:42,720 --> 00:37:44,360
This, too.

501
00:37:46,270 --> 00:37:48,460
Just pay me back later.

502
00:37:49,060 --> 00:37:51,120
Thanks.

503
00:37:51,120 --> 00:37:53,140
You're here to buy books, too?

504
00:37:54,800 --> 00:37:56,976
Math in our second year has gotten a lot harder,

505
00:37:56,976 --> 00:37:59,910
so I bought two extra exercise books to practice.

506
00:37:59,910 --> 00:38:03,870
I heard that after you transferred to the art class, you've been studying really hard.

507
00:38:03,870 --> 00:38:07,270
- If you ever need help with anything... 
 - Song Cong,

508
00:38:07,270 --> 00:38:11,450
is there nothing in your life besides studying?

509
00:38:13,770 --> 00:38:15,620
I just wanted to thank you for helping me earlier.

510
00:38:15,620 --> 00:38:18,810
I know. You don't want to owe me a favor, right?

511
00:38:36,540 --> 00:38:41,100
Every time before I went to tutoring, I would come here for a bit.

512
00:38:42,720 --> 00:38:46,540
Actually, back when I was taking TOEFL classes, I used to skip them and come here, too.

513
00:38:47,350 --> 00:38:49,700
You? Skipping class?

514
00:38:50,640 --> 00:38:53,090
Why wouldn't I?

515
00:38:57,190 --> 00:38:59,750
Everyone thinks I'm too perfect.

516
00:39:00,280 --> 00:39:02,630
Even Xi Chi and Huan Er do.

517
00:39:03,729 --> 00:39:05,729
What's up with you three?

518
00:39:06,390 --> 00:39:07,930
Nothing.

519
00:39:07,930 --> 00:39:09,650
Everything's fine.

520
00:39:13,100 --> 00:39:17,980
Honestly, I think there's still some misunderstanding between you guys.

521
00:39:21,750 --> 00:39:25,740
Last time, I said some things that were a bit too much.

522
00:39:27,540 --> 00:39:30,040
I thought about it afterward

523
00:39:30,910 --> 00:39:34,080
and realized it was just me being too stubborn.

524
00:39:34,080 --> 00:39:37,552
My family's housekeeper once told me

525
00:39:37,552 --> 00:39:40,020
that I bottle things up too much.

526
00:39:40,580 --> 00:39:41,921
I get it.

527
00:39:41,921 --> 00:39:44,960
Maybe if I just talked about it, everything would be fine.

528
00:39:45,880 --> 00:39:48,030
But I just can't get the words out.

529
00:39:53,774 --> 00:39:55,754
Actually, I'm the same way.

530
00:39:58,680 --> 00:40:02,040
Do you remember when you asked me why I thought your essays were good?

531
00:40:02,870 --> 00:40:11,090
It's because you always manage to express things that I don't know how to put into words.

532
00:40:13,790 --> 00:40:18,040
Then do you know why I just told you all those things from my heart?

533
00:40:19,418 --> 00:40:21,228
Why?

534
00:40:23,520 --> 00:40:25,690
Because I like you.

535
00:40:28,566 --> 00:40:30,506
What did you say?

536
00:40:32,292 --> 00:40:36,882
I said... I will become someone as amazing as you.

537
00:40:55,480 --> 00:40:56,991
Huan Er.

538
00:40:56,991 --> 00:41:00,420
- Aunt Lin. 
 - Here, have some water. It's hot, isn't it?

539
00:41:00,420 --> 00:41:01,540
Not too bad.

540
00:41:01,540 --> 00:41:04,020
There are quite a few people today.

541
00:41:04,540 --> 00:41:07,080
By the way, isn't Uncle Jing coming?

542
00:41:07,080 --> 00:41:08,270
He's on duty today.

543
00:41:08,270 --> 00:41:11,240
He'll come over as soon as his shift ends.

544
00:41:14,670 --> 00:41:16,170
Coach Li is over there.

545
00:41:16,170 --> 00:41:18,890
I'll go ask him about today's recruitment.

546
00:41:18,890 --> 00:41:20,390
All right.

547
00:41:29,910 --> 00:41:32,020
Here, drink some water.

548
00:41:32,020 --> 00:41:33,540
Thanks.

549
00:41:48,460 --> 00:41:50,500
Give me your hand.

550
00:41:50,500 --> 00:41:52,060
What for?

551
00:41:53,100 --> 00:41:56,680
My mom made me wear this red string since I was little.

552
00:41:56,680 --> 00:41:59,180
Consider it me sharing some of my luck with you.

553
00:42:00,140 --> 00:42:02,570
It should help a bit, right?

554
00:42:09,020 --> 00:42:12,790
Are you really giving me something so important?

555
00:42:12,790 --> 00:42:15,710
It's not a gift, just a temporary loan.

556
00:42:15,710 --> 00:42:18,360
If you like it, I'll make you another one later.

557
00:42:23,233 --> 00:42:24,683
Thanks.

558
00:42:26,390 --> 00:42:28,960
But don't worry.

559
00:42:28,960 --> 00:42:32,307
Now that I'm back in the game, I'm going to dominate the field.

